"ğŸ§ Common interview mistakes and how to avoid them\n\nğŸ‘‰ Lack of preparation\nCandidates often fail to research the company. Read up on their history, mission, and recent news. This shows genuine interest and can set you apart.\n\nğŸ‘‰ Overlooking the job description\nMake sure you understand the role requirements deeply. Highlight how your experience and skills align with what they need.\n\nğŸ‘‰ Poor body language\nSlouching, avoiding eye contact, or fidgeting can send negative signals. Practise confident, calm, and positive body language.\n\nğŸ‘‰ Talking too much (or too little)\nAim for balanced responses. Be concise but provide enough detail to showcase your abilities. It's a conversation, not a monologue.\n\nğŸ‘‰ Not asking questions\nShow curiosity and engagement by asking insightful questions about the role and the company. It shows you're seriously considering the position.\n\nğŸ‘‰ Ignoring cultural fit\nResearching the company's culture can help you assess if you'd thrive there. Mention how your values align with theirs.\n\nRemember, interviews are as much about fit as they are about skills. Be prepared, be yourself, and good luck!\n\nFeel free to share your own interview tips in the comments or visitfor more advice.\n\nâ€¦more"
